projects.name: Image Denoising Using Deep Learning
projects.description: Denoising images is crucial for enhancing resolution, pixel count, and contrast, ensuring pleasant visual experiences. Techniques like Autoencoder CNN and Matrix Factorization U-net (MFU) are employed for noise removal. Autoencoder CNN focuses on increasing network width rather than depth for improved denoising. Proposed work involves implementing Autoencoder CNN and MFU on Synthetic Gaussian Noise dataset.

projects.name: Osteoporosis Diagnosis through Segmentation and Classification
projects.description: A prevalent bone disorder characterized by reduced bone density and increased susceptibility to fractures. Integration of Transformers for intricate visual segmentation of digital knee X-ray images. Employing pre-trained models like VGG-19, U-Net, and RESNET for feature extraction. Integration of pre-trained models and transfer learning techniques to discern variations in osteoporosis severity.

projects.name: Company Management System
projects.description: A company management system using JSP (JavaServer Pages) and Servlets is a web-based application designed to help manage various aspects of a companys operations. The application typically interacts with a relational database management system (RDBMS) such as MySQL or Oracle for storing and retrieving data related to employees, customers, products, transactions, etc.

projects.name: Todo-App Using Mern Stack
projects.description: The MERN Todo App utilizes MongoDB for scalable data storage and Express.js for efficient backend API development, enabling CRUD operations. React.js powers the dynamic frontend interface with React components, while Node.js manages concurrent requests for optimal performance and scalability.

experiences.description: Created dynamic applications using core and advanced Java concepts in Eclipse IDE. Developed entire web pages for projects using JSP and Servlets, with data stored in Oracle database. Java Concepts used: Html And CSS for Frontend, JSP And Servlets for backend, Oracle for storage.
